local a={"Win a hand after you declared Riichi; You may declare Riichi when you achieve Tenpai (ready hand) at Menzenchin (closed hand)","Win a hand without any Terminal Tiles (1-Man/9-Man, 1-Pin/9-Pin, 1-Sou/9-Sou, Wind Tiles, and Dragon Tiles)","Win a hand by Tsumo (drawing the winning tile) at Menzenchin (closed hand)","Win a hand with a Triplet of Player Wind","Win a hand with a Triplet of Round Wind","Win a hand with a Triplet of Dragon Tile (White, Green or Red)","Win a hand with four Sequences and one non-Yakuhai Pair, plus the potential winning tiles must be tiles from both side of a Sequence","Win a hand with two identical Sequences","Call a Ron (declare winning) on another player’s Kan (when you have a Tenpai for Thirteen Orphans, you can call on a Closed Kan)","Win a hand with the tile drawn from the Dead Wall after immediately calling a Kan","Win a hand by Tsumo (drawing the winning tile) with the last tile drawn from the Wall","Win a hand by calling Ron (declare winning) on the last discarded tile","Win a hand within 1 turn after declaring Riichi, in addition, draws/discards must not be interrupted by tile calls during that turn","The next tile immediately after the flipped Dora Indicator Tile","Red 5-Man, Red 5-Pin, Red 5-Sou","In 3-Player Mahjong, North Wind can be considered as a Dora after “Kita” is called (does not count as a Dora if North Wind remains in hand)","Call a Ron on the first tile discarded by another player to declare Riichi","Call a Ron on a tile discarded by another player who just called Kan","Win a hand by Tsumo or Ron with 4 open Chii, Pon, or Kan","Declare Riichi with your starting hand before any tiles are called","Win a hand with three Triplets with the same number out of the Number Tiles (Man, Pin, Sou)","Win a hand with three Quads","Win a hand with four Triplets or Quads","Win a hand with three closed Triplets or closed Quads","Win a hand with two Triplets out of the Dragon Tiles (White, Green or Red), plus a Pair of the third Dragon Tile","Win a hand with only Terminal Tiles (1-Man/9-Man, 1-Pin/9-Pin, 1-Sou/9-Sou, Wind Tiles, and Dragon Tiles)","Win a hand with seven different Pairs","Win a hand where every Sequence, Triplet and Pair contains at least one Terminal Tile","Win a hand with a complete Sequence of 1 through 9 (i.e. 123-Man, 456-Man, 789-Man)","Win a hand with three Sequences with the same numbers out of three different Number Tiles  (i.e. 123-Man, 123-Pin, 123-Sou)","Win a hand consists of Man, Pin, Sou, Wind, and Dragon tiles","Win a hand with 3 consecutive Triplets","Win a hand with two sets two identical Sequences","Win a hand with every Sequence, Triplet and Pair contains at least one 1 and 9 out of the Number Tiles (1-Man/9-Man, 1-Pin/9-Pin, 1-Sou/9-Sou)","Win a hand with tiles from only one of the three Number Tiles (Man, Pin or Sou) and Honor Tiles (Wind Tiles and Dragon Tiles)","Win a hand with three identical Sequences","Win a hand with tiles from only one of the three Number Tiles (Man, Pin or Sou)","When a game ends in Exhaustive Draw, you win with this Yaku if all your discarded tiles are Terminal Tiles and none were called by other players","Win a hand by Tsumo (drawing the winning tile) with the last tile drawn from the Wall, and that tile must be 1-Pin(5 Han)","Call a Ron on the last tile drawn from the Wall, and that tile must be 9-Pin(5 Han)","Win a hand by Tsumo as a dealer in the first turn with the first draw","Win a hand by Tsumo as a non-dealer in the first turn before any tiles are called","Win a hand with three Triplets or Quads of all the three Dragon Tiles","Win a hand with four closed Triplets","Win a hand with four Triplets and a Pair of the Honor Tiles (Wind Tiles and Dragon Tiles)","Win a hand with only green-colored tiles: 2-Sou/3-Sou/4-Sou/6-Sou/8-Sou and/or Green (F)","Win a hand with four Triplets and a Pair of 1 and 9 out of the Number Tiles (1-Man/9-Man, 1-Pin/9-Pin, 1-Sou/9-Sou)","Win a hand with one of each 13 Terminal Tiles, plus any tile matches one of them","Win a hand with three Triplets or Quads of the Wind Tiles, plus a pair of the fourth wind","Win a hand with four Quads","Win a hand with tiles from only one of the three Number Tiles in the order of “1112345678999”, plus any tile matches one of them","Call a Ron as a non-dealer in the first turn you draw a tile and before any tiles are called","Win a hand with 7 Pairs consist of 2-Pin to 8-Pin","Win a hand with 7 Pairs consist of 2-Sou to 8-Sou","Win a hand with 7 Pairs consist of 2-Man to 8-Man","Win a hand with Double Riichi as well as Under the Sea/River","Achieve Tenpai with four Closed Triplets already drawn (i.e. waiting for one remaining tile to form a Pair)","Achieve Tenpai with 13 different Terminal Tiles already drawn (i.e. waiting for 1 out of 13 possible tiles to win)","Achieve Tenpai with tiles from only one of the three Number Tiles in the order of “1112345678999” (i.e. waiting for 1 out of 9 possible tiles to win)","Win a hand with four Triplets or Quads of the Wind Tiles","Win a hand with 7 Pairs consist of only Word tiles","The game becomes a draw when each player discards the same Wind Tile in the first turn","The game becomes a draw when two or more players called for a total of four Quads","You have the option to declare a draw in the first turn if your hand consists of 9 different Terminal Tiles  before any tiles are called","The game becomes a draw when all players have declared Riichi","The basic winning hand that does not satisfy any Yaku (except bonus Yaku) in the Bloodshed Skirmish.","Win a hand with the tile drawn from the Dead Wall after immediately calling a Kan.","Win a hand with the discarded tile of another player who just called a Kan.","Win a hand when another player adds to an Open Triplet.","Win a hand by Ron or Tsumo with the last tile drawn from the Wall.","Have 4 of the same tiles, counting Hand and callings (including Kans).","Have 4 sets of Triplets or Kans.","Have tiles from only one of the three suits (Man/Pin/Sou).","7 sets of Pairs (same pairs are allowed).","Have only the 4 sets of Sequences and Triplets of Terminals + Pair of Terminals.","Tsumo or Ron with four callings.","A Full Flush consist of all triplets.","All Triplets with all of the tiles numbered 2, 5, or 8.","Seven Pairs with two of the same pair.","A Full Flush consist of seven pairs.","A Full Flush consist of Terminals in all sets.","Single Wait after 4 Triplets of Full Flush.","Win a hand by Tsumo as a dealer in the first turn with the first draw.","Win a hand by Tsumo as a non-dealer in the first turn before any tiles are called.","A Full Flush consist of seven pairs with two same pairs.","Call a Kan for 4 times.","Call a Kan for 4 times and win a hand with Full Flush"}return a